OAO Novolipetsk Steel, owned by
Russian billionaire  Vladimir Lisin , rose to the highest level in
more than a week after announcing it agreed to buy out Duferco
Group from the companiesâ€™ equally owned joint venture.  The shares climbed 2.7 percent to 115.19 rubles as of 11:50
a.m. in Moscow, the strongest intraday price since April 13.  Novolipetsk agreed to pay $600 million for its half of the
Steel Invest and Finance venture, the company said in a
statement today. The joint venture controls seven rolling mills
